President Trump and President Macron met at the United Nations Headquarters in New York to discuss various topics including trade, military and defense, terrorism, and common security. President Macron expressed his condolences for the victims of Hurricane Florence and emphasized the need to work together on issues such as terrorism and the situation in the Middle East. Both leaders expressed their mutual respect and friendship, with President Trump mentioning the special celebration held at the White House to honor President Macron and France. They also discussed future plans for meetings, with President Macron inviting President Trump to visit Paris in November.